(3254, 1, '2015-11-27 09:22:30', '2015-11-27 09:22:30', '<dl class="faqs">\r\n                <dt class="hover">How Can I set my homepage to a static one like on theme''s demo page?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">\r\n                    Make sure you have assigned "Homepage" template to the page you want to set as your static home page.\r\n                    After setting the corresponding template and saving it go to Settings » Reading on your admin area \r\n                    (Screenshot 32). For the option "Front page displays" choose the page you have assigned "Home page" template to \r\n                    from the dropdown list (screenshot 33).\r\n                    <div class="frame bottom10 alignleft" style="width:140px">\r\n                        <img src="../screenshots/reading_settings.png" alt="Reading Menu">\r\n                        <p class="smalltext">Screenshot 32: Reading</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                     <div class="frame bottom10 alignright" style="margin-left:4px">\r\n                        <img src="../screenshots/rs_inner.png" alt="Reading Settings">\r\n                        <p class="smalltext">Screenshot 33: Reading Settings</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="clear"></div>\r\n                </dd>\r\n           \r\n                <dt class="hover">After importing the sample content, footer widgets are stacked, what''s wrong?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">\r\n                    Go to Appearance =&gt; widgets in your admin panel and remove all widgets from the sidebar called "Footer widget 1".\r\n                    Once done, assign your own widgets for footer, just remember the rule : 1 Sidebar =&gt; 1 widget.\r\n                </dd>\r\n                <dt>How do I display slider on homepage and how I choose which one to use?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">\r\n                	To display slider on homepage, make sure you''ve followed the previous point of this FAQ list (setting static homepage).\r\n                    For slider choice, the option is available on admin panel''s Alcatron =&gt; Homepage tab. Additional info about sliders can be found in \r\n                    documentation''s <a href="theme-options.html#generalsettings">corresponding section</a>.\r\n                </dd>\r\n                \r\n                <dt class="hover">What are the featured image sizes for for blog/portfolio thumbs and slider?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">\r\n                      <p>Portfolio (4 columns) -  269 x 136 pixels</p>\r\n                      <p>Portfolio (3 columns) -  365 x 236 pixels</p>\r\n                      <p>Blog (1 Column)  -  740 x 350 pixels</p>\r\n					  <p>Blog (1 Column, alternative)  -  357 x 234 pixels</p>\r\n					  <p>Blog (2 Columns)  -  357 x 169 pixels</p>\r\n					  <p>Blog (3 columns) -  260 x 170 pixels</p>\r\n                </dd>\r\n               \r\n                <dt class="hover">I have set up portfolio categories, made items but nothing shows up. What''s wrong?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">\r\n                    Once you''ve done adding categories and assigned these categories to corresponding items,\r\n                    go to portfolio page, make sure you''ve assigned it one of 3 available portfolio templates\r\n                    and on the page''s settings select all the checkboxes for the categories you want to show up \r\n                    in the page. Please note you can assign one category per item.\r\n                </dd>\r\n                <dt>How can I insert the social buttons in the header like in your page?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">Please check the <a href="shortcodes.html#social">shortcodes page</a> for a detailed info on this.</dd>\r\n               	<dt>How can I set the twitter widget correclty?</dt>\r\n                <dd style="display: none;">\r\n					Please check the <a savefrom_lm="1" savefrom_lm_index="0" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iL4b3Tiwy1I">screencast on Youtube</a><span style="padding: 0; margin: 0; margin-left: 5px;"><a savefrom_lm_is_link="1" savefrom_lm="1" style="background-image: url(&quot;data:image/gif;base64,&quot;); background-repeat: no-repeat; width: 16px; height: 16px; display: inline-block; border: medium none; text-decoration: none; padding: 0px; position: relative;" title="Get a direct link" target="_blank" href="http://savefrom.net/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DiL4b3Tiwy1I&amp;utm_source=ff-sf&amp;utm_medium=extensions&amp;utm_campaign=link_modifier"></a></span> to have it set up correctly.\r\n					<iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/iL4b3Tiwy1I?feature=player_detailpage" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="360" width="640"></iframe>\r\n				</dd>\r\n            </dl>', 'FAQs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3144-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-27 09:22:30', '2015-11-27 09:22:30', '', 3144, 'http://sdu.ucsc.lk/govtfactory/3144-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
